title: "No suitable videos found" attempting to "Extract Outlier Frames"

labels.name: howtousedlc
labels.description: issue regarding the use of DeepLabCut

body:
**Your Operating system and DeepLabCut version**
OS: Windows 10
DLC: 2.2b8
anaconda-env: tensorflow:1.15.5, wxpython:4.0.2

**Describe the problem**

I can't find the "Tracking Method" GUI button, in my "Analyze Video" tab.

This is what the tabs look like for me, which differ from the GUI in the YouTube videos (which have "convert to tracklets" button).

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/76114144/112392740-88ff3180-8cbf-11eb-933c-808dd8a133ed.png)
vs.
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/76114144/112391522-a92df100-8cbd-11eb-9764-1bcfba54cd50.png)

I am also missing tabs in the GUI like "refine tracklets"

________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________

I have trained a the network using 80 labelled frames, with 1,030,000 iterations.

Analyzing a new video "C2773.mp4", produced these 3 files:
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/76114144/112391791-0b86f180-8cbe-11eb-8870-94aa0628f777.png)
1. .h file
2. resnet.mp4
3. pickle file

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/76114144/112391936-48eb7f00-8cbe-11eb-92fa-6556a12e4dce.png)
When I select the resnet.mp4 in "Extract Outlier Frames", (using the "jump" algorithm) I get this error:

`(DLC) C:\Windows\system32>python -m deeplabcut
2021-03-24 16:25:43.957770: I tensorflow/stream_executor/platform/default/dso_loader.cc:44] Successfully opened dynamic library cudart64_100.dll
Starting GUI...
No suitable videos found in ['E:\\ShArEd\\Karyne Rats 2021\\Videos\\Winter 2021 (cut)\\Baseline v2\\C2773DLC_resnet_50_Baseline RatsMar18shuffle1_1030000_labeled.mp4']`

**How to Reproduce the problem**
Steps to reproduce the behavior:
1. Enter DLC env: activate DLC (I named the env "DLC", but it uses tensorflow-gpu)
1. Open DLC GUI: python -m deeplabcut
3. Import config file.
4. Extract outlier frames: select Resnet.mp4 (C2773DLC_resnet_50_Baseline RatsMar18shuffle1_1030000_labeled.mp4)
5. Specify the algorithm: 'jump' (this was default)
6. See error:
`(DLC) C:\Windows\system32>python -m deeplabcut
2021-03-24 16:25:43.957770: I tensorflow/stream_executor/platform/default/dso_loader.cc:44] Successfully opened dynamic library cudart64_100.dll
Starting GUI...
No suitable videos found in ['E:\\ShArEd\\Karyne Rats 2021\\Videos\\Winter 2021 (cut)\\Baseline v2\\C2773DLC_resnet_50_Baseline RatsMar18shuffle1_1030000_labeled.mp4']`


Thanks for your help in advance, this has been a great learning experience!
~ Simon
